28:20.829 --> 28:23.702
You and I have more in common
than you and Miller.

28:25.573 --> 28:29.620
His politics will divide
this country even further.

28:29.664 --> 28:33.363
But you and I can show America
that people can disagree

28:33.407 --> 28:37.063
and still work together
and get things done.

28:37.106 --> 28:39.065
I'd never give up
being a Republican.

28:39.108 --> 28:40.544
I'd never ask you to.

28:40.588 --> 28:43.199
I wouldn't support
all of your policies.

28:43.243 --> 28:45.636
All I'd ask
is that you hear me out.

28:45.680 --> 28:47.638
And I'd do the same with you.

28:47.682 --> 28:50.380
And when we disagree?

28:50.424 --> 28:51.793
You'll never have
to publicly support

28:51.817 --> 28:53.557
a policy you don't believe in.

28:53.601 --> 28:56.691
As long as you don't
publicly disagree, either.

28:58.911 --> 29:03.219
Look, I-I'm truly honored

29:03.263 --> 29:05.744
for this offer, Elizabeth,

29:05.787 --> 29:08.790
but no matter how you spin this,

29:08.834 --> 29:11.271
I would still be
abandoning my party.

29:13.447 --> 29:16.798
No, I appreciate the courage

29:16.842 --> 29:20.759
that it took you to ask me,
but I'm not that courageous.

29:29.158 --> 29:31.247
Good luck out there.

29:31.291 --> 29:33.119
You, too.

29:33.162 --> 29:34.468
Yeah.

29:39.429 --> 29:41.170
All I ask is that you lean

29:41.214 --> 29:43.390
on Senator Sheehan, Zack.

29:45.392 --> 29:48.134
Okay, thanks for your time.

29:48.177 --> 29:49.570
Who's next?

29:49.613 --> 29:50.808
Ma'am, General Kohl
wants you to know

29:50.832 --> 29:53.313
the countermeasures
against Iran have begun.

29:54.575 --> 29:56.292
Tell him I want a progress
report in an hour.

29:56.316 --> 29:58.535
Yes, ma'am.Sixty.

29:58.579 --> 30:00.624
We got to 60.What? Wait.

30:00.668 --> 30:02.864
How? Son of a bitch Girardi
came around after getting beaten

30:02.888 --> 30:05.281
like a redheaded stepchild
by Kristi Daniels.

30:05.325 --> 30:09.633
Not an hour after you talked to
her, she threatened to pull LCD

30:09.677 --> 30:11.374
and battery production
out of Florida.

30:11.418 --> 30:13.289
Boom!

30:13.333 --> 30:15.161
Mmm.

30:15.204 --> 30:17.641
Doesn't this make you want to
just stay being chief of staff?

30:17.685 --> 30:19.600
Have you no shame,
Madam President?

30:19.643 --> 30:20.906
No.
It's a big deal, Bess.

30:20.949 --> 30:22.579
I know.
Especially with all
the Iran noise.

30:22.603 --> 30:24.823
I know.
Mmm.

30:24.866 --> 30:26.825
Thanks, Mike.

30:32.352 --> 30:34.876
Hey. This is a surprise.

30:34.920 --> 30:37.618
I've got 15 minutes
till my next meeting.

30:37.661 --> 30:39.881
Yeah, I got ten.

30:41.230 --> 30:43.189
I love this jacket.

30:43.232 --> 30:46.453
Oh, well, it's a two-button
basket weave wool,

30:46.496 --> 30:48.237
which is very versatile.

30:48.281 --> 30:49.804
Are you mad at me about Roxanne?

30:49.848 --> 30:51.260
I just thought she had
some neat ideas,

30:51.284 --> 30:54.548
and y-you can always say no.

30:54.591 --> 30:56.550
But you do look good.

30:56.593 --> 30:58.465
How good?

31:01.250 --> 31:03.209
Follow me, FGOTUS.

31:03.252 --> 31:05.254
Yes, ma'am.

31:11.565 --> 31:13.915
Well, I hope that was fun,
because the good times are over.

31:13.959 --> 31:15.153
I was gone, like, ten minutes.

31:15.177 --> 31:17.484
Miller's threatening
to withdraw his support.

31:17.527 --> 31:18.746
That leaves us with 59 votes.

31:18.789 --> 31:20.574
And with that stupid
investigation going on,

31:20.617 --> 31:22.247
the lack of his vote looks like
retribution.Okay. I'll get into it.

31:22.271 --> 31:23.969
No, I'm on it, I'm on it.No.

31:24.012 --> 31:25.598
I have to do this myself. Madam President,
I really wouldn't. I...

31:25.622 --> 31:27.818
I know. I'm supposed to give the
marching orders and not march,

31:27.842 --> 31:29.844
I go that,
and I've been doing it,

31:29.888 --> 31:31.541
but now it is time
for the nuclear option.

31:31.585 --> 31:34.283
I'm not... I don't disagree, it's your
shirt's on inside out.

31:35.676 --> 31:36.895
I'm...

31:36.938 --> 31:38.331
I'll call the motorcade.

31:38.374 --> 31:40.376
Thank you.

31:46.382 --> 31:47.882
Valerie Guillen,
the reporter at The Chronicle

31:47.906 --> 31:49.746
who originally broke
the Senator Miller scandal

31:49.777 --> 31:51.735
is refusing to give up
her source,

31:51.779 --> 31:53.955
but she denies receiving... TAYLOR:
Senator Miller,

31:53.999 --> 31:55.879
I'm so sorry to interrupt.
The president just...

31:55.914 --> 31:56.958
Senator.

31:57.002 --> 31:59.569
Got a minute? Oh.

31:59.613 --> 32:01.267
Madam President. Of course.

32:01.310 --> 32:03.350
Ever since President McCord's
press conference...

32:03.747 --> 32:05.967
Four TVs. Thorough.

32:06.011 --> 32:08.796
I like to stay on top
of current events.

32:08.839 --> 32:11.799
Yeah.
Ma'am,

32:11.842 --> 32:14.410
would it be wrong to tell you
how ravishing you look?

32:14.454 --> 32:16.673
You mean because
I'm your president,

32:16.717 --> 32:18.066
or because it's creepy?

32:18.110 --> 32:20.503
Well, I just want
to get a good look at you

32:20.547 --> 32:23.419
because the Oval Office
ages you,

32:23.463 --> 32:26.988
especially with that
whole Iran business.

32:27.032 --> 32:29.077
You won't look the same
come next year.

32:29.121 --> 32:30.687
I got to give you credit.

32:30.731 --> 32:34.430
You are just as vulgar
in private as you are in public.

32:34.474 --> 32:36.955
Why are you here, ma'am?

32:36.998 --> 32:39.609
I need your vote on ESI.

32:39.653 --> 32:41.524
There are 40 other senators

32:41.568 --> 32:43.744
that you could be begging
to flip their vote,

32:43.787 --> 32:45.398
and you chose me?

32:45.441 --> 32:47.617
Those 40 others are opposed
for ideological reasons.

32:47.661 --> 32:49.619
You supported the bill
up until an hour ago.

32:49.663 --> 32:54.450
And you expect me
to be your white knight

32:54.494 --> 32:57.062
when your administration's
under a cloud.

32:57.105 --> 32:59.716
You must be pretty
desperate, ma'am.

32:59.760 --> 33:03.416
Prostrating yourself
instead of dispatching

33:03.459 --> 33:05.331
your little pit bull, Barnow,

33:05.374 --> 33:08.334
like you did to get
the Iran deal done.

33:08.377 --> 33:10.771
Losing hurts, doesn't it?

33:10.814 --> 33:12.903
You accused me
of collusion with Iran.

33:12.947 --> 33:16.385
I wanted to tell you
face-to-face, that's not true.

33:16.429 --> 33:19.475
Well, forgive me
if I'd rather wait

33:19.519 --> 33:21.042
for the results
of the investigation.

33:21.086 --> 33:23.653
I know you've been
cozy with Iran

33:23.697 --> 33:25.133
for years.

33:25.177 --> 33:28.006
Sometimes I wonder
just how cozy you got

33:28.049 --> 33:29.920
with Minister Javani.

33:29.964 --> 33:32.619
God, how low can you go?

33:32.662 --> 33:35.883
The lies you've been spewing
about that deal these past years

33:35.926 --> 33:38.059
have done nothing
for American security...

33:38.103 --> 33:39.669
I resent that, Madam. Too bad.

33:39.713 --> 33:42.107
Get your facts straight.

33:42.150 --> 33:44.500
Now, I'm not here
to relitigate that deal.

33:44.544 --> 33:46.067
What do you want?

33:46.111 --> 33:48.026
My reputation back!

33:49.984 --> 33:51.855
Committee assignments.

33:51.899 --> 33:54.119
That's up to your party.

33:54.162 --> 33:57.818
I want to be right by your
side for the bill signing,

33:57.861 --> 33:59.515
and I want to be
the first person

33:59.559 --> 34:00.710
whose hand you shake and thank,

34:00.734 --> 34:03.389
and then I want you
to personally

34:03.432 --> 34:05.695
lobby Ramirez and Hopkins

34:05.739 --> 34:07.871
to restore my
committee assignments.

34:10.960 --> 34:13.399
Well done, Madam President.

34:13.442 --> 34:14.878
That's how
the sausage gets made.

34:14.922 --> 34:17.620
Enough to make me want
to go full-on vegan.

34:17.664 --> 34:19.708
You got it done.
Next order of business,

34:19.753 --> 34:22.103
updated shortlist of the
new chief of staff options.

34:22.147 --> 34:24.714
Who do you like?

34:24.757 --> 34:26.976
I like this.

34:27.021 --> 34:30.416
I-I don't want
to break in anyone new.

34:30.458 --> 34:32.418
Tell that to Jay.

34:32.460 --> 34:34.942
You got to let that go.
If you will let me go.

34:43.472 --> 34:46.996
Ever since Gordon died,
I've been reevaluating things.

34:47.041 --> 34:51.654
He was the only totally pure
and honest part of my life,

34:51.697 --> 34:53.482
which, being in D.C.,
isn't saying much,

34:53.525 --> 34:55.092
but still.

34:55.136 --> 34:57.443
I just accepted him
for who he was.

34:57.486 --> 35:00.010
If he... if he took a crap
on my bath mat

35:00.054 --> 35:02.839
or tried to hump
the golden across the street,

35:02.883 --> 35:06.016
I just, I always knew
he was being true to himself,

35:06.060 --> 35:08.062
in the moment.

35:11.544 --> 35:14.634
It was his most
profound gift to me.

35:17.637 --> 35:20.161
A lesson in how to live,

35:20.205 --> 35:22.642
and I'm-I'm trying
to honor that.

35:24.818 --> 35:26.559
Look, I would...

35:26.602 --> 35:28.778
I would stand in front
of a bullet train for you, Bess,

35:28.822 --> 35:31.172
which I can now

35:31.216 --> 35:34.958
with the infrastructure part
of the ESI bill,

35:35.002 --> 35:37.918
but I have to trust my gut
on this.

35:41.008 --> 35:44.011
Okay, I'll stop begging.

35:44.054 --> 35:46.056
Thank you.

35:50.235 --> 35:53.803
Aren't you gonna
miss this office?

35:53.847 --> 35:55.283
Oh, I'm not giving this up.

35:55.327 --> 35:57.677
The new guy can get another one.
I was here first.

35:59.853 --> 36:01.507
What?

36:01.550 --> 36:04.988
You just made me realize
who I want to replace you.

36:21.831 --> 36:25.052
Congrats on your first victory
with the ESI bill.

36:27.054 --> 36:28.664
You get two more, tops,

36:28.708 --> 36:30.971
and that's if this
Iran investigation

36:31.014 --> 36:32.581
doesn't cripple you.

36:32.625 --> 36:34.540
It's good to see you, too,
Russell.

36:34.583 --> 36:36.542
Lawn looks nice.

36:36.585 --> 36:40.023
Yeah. Carol fired
the gardener

36:40.067 --> 36:42.243
so I'd have something
relaxing to do.

36:42.287 --> 36:46.029
It's supposed to be Zen
or something.

36:46.073 --> 36:48.597
Nobody tells you about weeds.

36:48.641 --> 36:50.599
Do you realize what a
pain in the ass they are?

36:50.643 --> 36:53.298
They never stop.
They're like lobbyists.

36:53.341 --> 36:55.778
Well, then, I'll get
right to the point.

36:55.822 --> 36:58.738
I'm sorry to drop in unannounced

36:58.781 --> 37:01.044
but I knew
that if I gave you a heads-up

37:01.088 --> 37:03.917
then Carol would
run interference.

37:03.960 --> 37:05.875
Oh.

37:05.919 --> 37:08.704
You want me
to do something... stressful.

37:08.748 --> 37:10.706
Just temporarily.

37:10.750 --> 37:13.927
I want you to step in
as my chief of staff

37:13.970 --> 37:15.929
for a transition period.

37:15.972 --> 37:18.323
I know you've already
given eight years

37:18.366 --> 37:21.761
of this job to Dalton,
and you may be over it,

37:21.804 --> 37:25.112
but this moment
in time is going to determine

37:25.155 --> 37:27.680
how effective
I am going forward,

37:27.723 --> 37:29.769
and...

37:29.812 --> 37:31.771
I really need you.

37:31.814 --> 37:34.730
Don't answer,
because I-I... I know you got

37:34.774 --> 37:39.126
to talk it over with Carol,
and if it's "no," I understand.

37:40.388 --> 37:42.608
I had to ask.

37:54.881 --> 37:56.709
Carol?!

37:56.752 --> 37:58.754
Call the gardener!

38:00.756 --> 38:02.715
I also need to thank

38:02.758 --> 38:04.847
Senator Beauregard Miller

38:04.891 --> 38:08.329
whose decisive vote
made this day possible.

38:08.373 --> 38:10.070
Senator,

38:10.113 --> 38:12.725
your bold leadership

38:12.768 --> 38:14.727
on this historic bill

38:14.770 --> 38:16.729
will always be remembered.

38:16.772 --> 38:18.774
Thank you,
and thank you to everyone

38:18.818 --> 38:21.124
who came together
to get this done.

38:45.192 --> 38:48.326
And that right there is how you
do the first 100 days in office.

38:48.369 --> 38:49.433
Congratulations,
Madam President.

38:49.457 --> 38:50.893
It's a momentous victory.

38:50.937 --> 38:52.436
Well, I couldn't have done it
without the both of you.

38:52.460 --> 38:55.202
Well, that's true. Especially you,
FGOTUS.

38:55.245 --> 38:57.335
It's been a pleasure
making history with you.

38:58.945 --> 39:00.338
Okay.

39:00.381 --> 39:01.774
Enjoy it while it lasts,

39:01.817 --> 39:05.168
'cause this Iran debacle
is gonna be a nightmare.

39:05.212 --> 39:07.301
They are gonna
pull out all the stops,

39:07.345 --> 39:10.435
milk every bit
of lifeblood out of it.

39:10.478 --> 39:12.088
Drink, Russell?

39:12.132 --> 39:14.134
Just a small one.

39:15.135 --> 39:17.355
Well, I want to taste it.

39:19.400 --> 39:21.359
Thank you.

39:23.491 --> 39:24.927
Unto the breach.

39:24.971 --> 39:26.364
Oh.
Hear, hear.

39:27.452 --> 39:29.410
Oh, I'm taking my office back.

39:29.454 --> 39:31.151
What?

39:32.195 --> 39:33.849
I was here first.

39:36.199 --> 39:37.418
The American Experiment

39:37.462 --> 39:39.725
is about giving everyone
a way forward

39:39.768 --> 39:41.291
even when we disagree.

39:41.335 --> 39:46.035
In fact, disagreement is
the hallmark of our democracy.

39:46.079 --> 39:49.212
We respect our Constitution

39:49.256 --> 39:52.259
by respecting
our fellow citizens,

39:52.302 --> 39:55.044
even when
we don't get everything we want,

39:55.088 --> 39:57.917
even when we disagree
passionately.

39:57.960 --> 40:00.267
Thatis democracy.

40:03.923 --> 40:06.012
Now one of my opponents,

40:06.055 --> 40:09.058
he hasn't liked what he's been
reading about himself lately,

40:09.102 --> 40:11.974
so he's lashed out
at the media in ways

40:12.018 --> 40:15.500
that I believe undermine
freedom of the press,

40:15.543 --> 40:19.852
which is enshrined
in our Constitution.

40:21.897 --> 40:24.509
And he has engaged in attacks...

40:24.552 --> 40:28.774
Personal attacks...
Against his opponents

40:28.817 --> 40:32.430
that are not only irrelevant
to important policy debates,

40:32.473 --> 40:34.910
but are meaningless distractions

40:34.954 --> 40:39.132
that are beneath the dignity
of the office we seek.

40:41.177 --> 40:44.572
Anyone running for public office

40:44.616 --> 40:46.531
who tries to bully his opponents

40:46.574 --> 40:49.055
is not just disrespecting them,

40:49.098 --> 40:51.536
but disrespecting America

40:51.579 --> 40:55.278
and the rights
and values that we stand for.

40:57.324 --> 41:00.501
Anyone who questions
our basic freedoms

41:00.545 --> 41:03.112
because they don't like
what's coming out

41:03.156 --> 41:04.897
about themselves in the press

41:04.940 --> 41:08.030
isn't just disrespecting
our Constitution.

41:08.074 --> 41:10.119
He is rejecting it.

41:12.557 --> 41:14.950
Eroding our core values
and rights

41:14.994 --> 41:18.345
will lead us down a dark road
toward autocracy.

41:19.651 --> 41:22.480
Democracy means
that we stand united,

41:22.523 --> 41:25.918
even when we sit
on different sides of the aisle.

41:25.961 --> 41:28.486
We fight for what we believe in,

41:28.529 --> 41:30.575
but we fight fair.

41:30.618 --> 41:34.535
With decency and dignity
and respect.

41:35.667 --> 41:37.625
Now I realize...

41:37.669 --> 41:40.149
I realize
that these are just words.

41:40.193 --> 41:42.848
So how can I put these words
into action?

41:42.891 --> 41:44.545
How?!

41:44.589 --> 41:47.156
Well, I'd like

41:47.200 --> 41:49.376
to introduce you
to my running mate.

41:49.419 --> 41:52.988
I am humbled and honored
that he decided to join me,

41:53.032 --> 41:55.164
especially
because he and I have been known

41:55.208 --> 41:57.471
to be political rivals.

41:57.515 --> 42:00.300
Well, we fought
for what we believe in,

42:00.343 --> 42:02.650
and we fought
through our differences,

42:02.694 --> 42:05.348
and we got things done.

42:07.263 --> 42:09.222
And we will continue

42:09.265 --> 42:11.050
to rise above our differences

42:11.093 --> 42:13.400
on behalf of all Americans.

42:13.443 --> 42:15.533
I am so proud

42:15.576 --> 42:19.537
to introduce the next vice
president of the United States,

42:19.580 --> 42:22.365
Senator Carlos Morejon.

42:22.409 --> 42:25.630
♪ Who can I believe in?

42:25.673 --> 42:29.242
♪ I'm kneeling on the floor

42:29.285 --> 42:31.636
♪ There has to be a force

42:31.679 --> 42:34.943
♪ Who do I phone?

42:35.727 --> 42:38.947
♪ The stars are out
and shining ♪

42:38.991 --> 42:42.255
♪ But all I really want
to know ♪

42:42.298 --> 42:46.041
♪ Oh, won't you

42:46.085 --> 42:47.956
♪ Show me the way

42:48.000 --> 42:50.219
♪ Every day

42:50.263 --> 42:52.221
♪ I want you...

